articles.title: DeSantis' office says salaries of officials who require masks for students may be withheld
articles.description: The office of Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis said the state board of education could withhold salaries from school superintendents and others who require masks for all.
articles.content:
Florida school superintendents who require masks for students without giving them a way to opt out could have their salaries withheld, Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis' office said Monday
